 :tx/rationale "Create task: META-12: Hebbian significance accumulation from metabolic data — high-novelty transaction co-occurrences strengthen entity associations (INV-QUERY-003). BACKGROUND: SEED.md §7 says 'connections that are traversed together strengthen together.' INV-QUERY-003 (significance accumulation) exists but has no data source — the access log separation (AS-007) prevents query-driven feedback loops. Metabolic transaction data provides the missing source: entities that co-occur in HIGH-NOVELTY transactions (delta-crystallization > 0.2 or delta-implementation > 0.2) get their significance scores boosted. This is Hebbian learning: 'neurons that fire together wire together.' APPROACH: (1) When transact() computes metabolic deltas and the combined delta is high (> threshold): extract all entities touched by this transaction. (2) For each entity pair (e_i, e_j) in the transaction: increment a co-occurrence counter. (3) The significance function (used by seed assembly, reconciliation, routing) reads co-occurrence data to boost entities that frequently appear together in productive transactions. (4) Implementation: new function hebbian_boost(store, entity) -> f64 that queries :tx/delta-crystallization > 0 transactions, finds co-occurring entities, returns boosted significance. (5) Wire into seed's StateEntry scoring (seed.rs, relevance computation) and guidance's knowledge_relevance_scan. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Entities in high-delta transactions get higher significance. (B) Entities in zero-delta transactions get no boost. (C) Significance is monotonically non-decreasing (Hebbian LTP). (D) No feedback loop from query to significance (AS-007 maintained). DEPENDS-ON: META-5 (t-ba14c7a9). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs + seed.rs. TRACES TO: INV-QUERY-003, INV-SEED-005, SEED.md §7."
